---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Viking Range Repair | Southern California | Professional 7 Series, Tuxedo, 5 Series, Dual-Fuel";
const description = "Viking range repair across Southern California. Professional 7 Series dual-fuel (VDR7488) and all-gas (VGR7488), 5 Series (VGRC5486), Tuxedo Collection, Tuscany. Spark module VKPA020047, F02 RTD, surface igniter, bake element service. Factory-trained, post-warranty specialists. $89 diagnostic waived with repair. Call (424) 325-0520.";

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/viking-range-repair/#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Viking Range Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/viking-range-repair/",
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$$"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Viking Range Repair",
    "provider": { "@type": "LocalBusiness", "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My Viking burner clicks but won't light, what's wrong?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most common Viking range call. Diagnostic order in frequency: (1) burner is wet or greasy from recent cleaning, wipe the igniter electrode and spark target, let fully dry 2-4 hours, retest; (2) grease or food debris in the burner port blocking gas flow, clean with a pin or small needle; (3) burner cap misaligned, Viking caps are more finicky than most; reseat carefully so the notch aligns with the ignition electrode; (4) spark module VKPA020047 failed, this is the single component that controls spark delivery to all burners, and when it fails individual burners lose sparking capability while others keep working; (5) individual igniter electrode cracked or burnt. Spark module replacement $285-$425; individual igniter $185-$275. We diagnose which cause before ordering parts. Swap test: if rotating a known-good knob fires all burners including the failing one, the issue is at the specific knob/switch, not the module."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "F02 error code on my Viking oven",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "F02 is the RTD (resistance temperature detector) probe fault, the oven temperature sensor has drifted or opened. Symptoms: oven temperature reads wrong, oven may overshoot or undershoot set temperature by 25-75°F, self-clean may abort. Diagnostic: check RTD resistance at room temperature (should read ~1080-1100 ohms at 77°F per Viking spec), inspect probe connector at the rear of the oven cavity, verify wire harness to the EOC is intact. Probe replacement $165-$245, 45-minute job. On older Viking Professional ranges (pre-2015), F02 also appears from degraded wire-harness connectors, we clean and retest before replacing the probe, about 20% resolve at the connector level."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My Viking dual-fuel oven is running hot, temperature inaccurate",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Viking 7 Series dual-fuel (VDR7486, VDR7488) temperature problems are almost always electrical, the oven side is electric even though the burners are gas. Four causes in order: (1) RTD probe drift (see F02 above, $165-$245); (2) bake element partially shorted, heating more than specified ($225-$325); (3) convection fan stalled, on VDR7486 and similar, a stalled fan motor causes heat to concentrate in localized hot spots; symptom is one rack burning while another undercooks; replacement $285-$420; (4) door gasket degraded, causing heat to escape and the thermostat to overshoot to compensate, replacement $285-$420. A 25-75°F overshoot or wide swing range usually points to the thermostat or RTD; localized hot spots point to the convection fan; gradual undershoot points to gasket or bake element."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Viking range repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Diagnostic is $89, waived with repair. Typical Viking range repairs: spark module (VKPA020047) $285-$425, surface igniter electrode $185-$275, gas valve assembly $425-$640, burner tube $165-$240, oven igniter (all-gas models) $245-$340, bake element (dual-fuel) $225-$325, broil element $245-$345, RTD temperature probe $165-$245, convection fan motor $285-$420, oven door hinge (single) $185-$265, oven door gasket $285-$420, glass door inner pane $345-$520, Electronic Oven Control (EOC) board $640-$920, control knob (single) $45-$75, thermostat $185-$265, burner cap replacement $65-$95. Labor and parts quoted before work starts."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you service Viking Professional 5 Series EOC board issues?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, Electronic Oven Control board issues on the 2019-2022 Professional 5 Series (VGRC5486GSS and similar) are an increasingly common call. Symptoms: temperature display blank or corrupted, self-clean fails to start, convection mode doesn't activate, or the oven runs continuously regardless of setpoint. EOC is the oven's main computer, replacement $640-$920, 90-minute job. We verify through service-mode diagnostics that the EOC is the actual failure before ordering; sometimes an RTD probe fault or wiring issue triggers symptoms that mimic EOC failure. The 2023+ Professional 5 Series units have revised control hardware with fewer of these issues."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's the difference between Viking dual-fuel and all-gas for service?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Big difference. Dual-fuel ranges (VDR prefix, 7 Series and 5 Series dual-fuel variants) have gas burners on top and an electric oven underneath. The oven uses bake element ($225-$325), broil element ($245-$345), convection fan motor ($285-$420), and RTD temperature probe ($165-$245), all electrical components. All-gas ranges (VGR prefix) use a gas oven with a glow-bar oven igniter ($245-$340) and gas safety valve instead of electrical heating. Service philosophy differs: dual-fuel ovens are more precise for baking because electric heat is easier to control; all-gas ovens have more temperature drift and need igniter/safety-valve service more often. Service costs are similar overall; component mix is different."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">LA · Orange · Ventura · San Bernardino · Riverside Counties</p>
        <h1>Viking Range Repair</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">Factory-trained service on Viking Professional 7 Series (dual-fuel VDR and all-gas VGR), Professional 5 Series, Tuxedo Collection, legacy Tuscany, and pre-2015 DSC Professional platform. 30"-60" widths. Spark module VKPA020047, F02 RTD diagnostics, convection fan, bake/broil element, EOC board service. Post-warranty specialists on 5-to-20-year-old Vikings.</p>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn-primary">☎ {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline">Book Online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-img-wrap">
        <div class="hero-img-placeholder">
          <p>Viking Range Repair</p>
          <p>Across Southern California</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🏅</span> BHGS Licensed #A49573</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🛡</span> Fully Insured</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">⚡</span> Same Day Available</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🔩</span> OEM Parts on Truck</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">💬</span> $89 Diagnostic, Waived With Repair</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">About this service</p>
      <h2>Viking invented the residential pro range. We keep them running for decades.</h2>
      <p>The Viking Professional range is the brand's signature product, commercial-style sealed burners, cast-iron grates, the red control knob that's been the visual trademark since 1987. In LA, Viking ranges anchor kitchens from 30-inch Wilshire condos to 60-inch Malibu estates with double ovens and a built-in griddle. Most LA Viking ranges we service are 5-to-20 years old, units installed during the 2005-2020 luxury kitchen wave that are now past warranty but have another decade or more of service life with component-level attention.</p>
      <p>Viking range service requires specific knowledge that general repair techs often lack. The <strong>spark module part VKPA020047</strong>, the single component that controls ignition across all burners, is the root cause of most "clicking but won't light" calls and is often mis-diagnosed. The <strong>F02 RTD temperature probe fault</strong> is the most common oven-temperature complaint and has a specific diagnostic sequence that a factory-trained tech handles in one visit. Viking dual-fuel vs all-gas architecture differences matter, VDR prefix (dual-fuel) has an electric oven with bake element, broil element, and convection fan, while VGR prefix (all-gas) uses a glow-bar oven igniter. We carry both schematics and common parts for both architectures on the truck.</p>
      <p>Most of our Viking range calls come from Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Brentwood, Pacific Palisades, Malibu, Hidden Hills, Calabasas, and the Pasadena foothills on LA's Westside; Newport Coast, Coto de Caza, Newport Beach, and Shady Canyon in Orange County; Westlake Village and Thousand Oaks in Ventura; and Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula wine-country estate kitchens in the Inland Empire. Same factory training as Viking Certified Service, faster response, lower labor rate than a post-warranty Viking Certified dispatch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── MODELS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Platforms and models</p>
      <h2>Viking range platforms we service</h2>

      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Professional 7 Series Dual-Fuel (Current Flagship)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">VDR7486GSS (48") · VDR7488BSS · VDR7366BSS (36") · VDR74824BSS (48" 4-burner + griddle)</p>
          <p>Current flagship dual-fuel, gas burners (up to 25,000 BTU), electric oven with VariSimmer 250°F-500°F convection, ProFlow convection system, Rapid Ready preheat. VDR7486 is the most common flagship configuration in LA. Electric oven side uses bake element ($225-$325), convection fan ($285-$420), RTD probe ($165-$245).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Professional 7 Series All-Gas</h3>
          <p class="model-list">VGR7488BSS (48") · VGR5488BSS · VGR74828BSS · VGR73626BSS (36") · VGR5366</p>
          <p>All-gas 7 Series, same sealed burners and rangetop architecture as dual-fuel, but gas oven with glow-bar oven igniter ($245-$340) and gas safety valve. Oven temperature is less precise than dual-fuel (wider swing range) but the all-gas platform has fewer electrical parts to fail over the long term.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Professional 5 Series</h3>
          <p class="model-list">VGRC5486GSS (48" gas) · VDRC5486GSS (dual-fuel) · VGRC5364 (36") · VDRC5486</p>
          <p>Mid-tier Professional, same sealed-burner commercial heritage, reduced feature set compared to 7 Series. 2019-2022 5 Series units are seeing increased EOC (Electronic Oven Control) board failures, the oven's main computer is the most common post-warranty replacement on this generation. 2023+ units have revised control hardware.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Tuxedo Collection</h3>
          <p class="model-list">VGR3646B(K) · VDR3646B(K) · VTU3646B (Tuxedo-specific trim)</p>
          <p>Matte-black aesthetic variant of Professional 7 and 5 Series. Same underlying platform as standard stainless versions, same spark module VKPA020047, same RTD probe, same oven elements, but black knobs and black trim instead of stainless + red. Service parts are identical to stainless equivalents except for visible trim pieces.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Tuscany (Legacy, Pre-2015)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">VITU4865 · VITU5305 · VITU5605 · VITSC4806 (Tuscany range-top)</p>
          <p>Discontinued premium line produced 2010-2015, Italian-influenced design language, color-accent options. Still found in Westside LA, Newport Beach, Westlake Village, and Rancho Cucamonga kitchens from that era. Parts availability is reduced, Viking no longer stocks all components, but our supplier network has most common items. We give honest repair-vs-replace assessments on Tuscany units that need major component work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Pre-Professional Legacy (DSC)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">DSC365-4GBK (36" dual-fuel) · DSC305 · DSC307 · DSC485-6GQ · DSC485-4GAFTER</p>
          <p>Pre-Professional Viking (Dynamic Cooking Systems platform, 1995-2008). 20-year-old DSC units still running in Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Newport Beach, Hidden Hills, and Temecula wine-country kitchens as original installs. We have the Viking service manual for DSC series and source common parts. Component-level repair pencils out against replacement through year 22-25 for these.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="footnote">Tuscany and DSC series parts availability is narrower than current production. We verify part availability before dispatch on these legacy models and give honest assessments if a critical component is no longer sourceable.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMMON PROBLEMS ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Common failures</p>
      <h2>The ten things that break on a Viking range</h2>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>1. Burner clicks but won't light, wet, greasy, or spark module failed</h3>
        <p>Most common Viking call. Diagnostic order: (1) burner wet from recent cleaning, wipe and dry 2-4 hours, free; (2) grease in burner port, clean with pin; (3) burner cap misaligned (Viking caps are finicky, reseat so notch aligns with ignition electrode); (4) spark module VKPA020047 failed, controls all burners, when it fails individual burners lose spark while others keep working. Swap test: rotate a known-good knob and watch if all burners fire including the failing one, if yes, module is fine, issue is at the specific knob/switch. Module $285-$425, individual igniter $185-$275.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>2. F02 RTD probe error on oven</h3>
        <p>Oven temperature sensor drifted or opened. Symptoms: temperature reads wrong, oven overshoots or undershoots 25-75°F, self-clean may abort. Diagnostic: test RTD resistance at room temperature (should read ~1080-1100 ohms at 77°F), inspect probe connector at rear of oven cavity, verify wire harness to EOC intact. Probe $165-$245, 45-minute job. On pre-2015 Viking Professionals, 20% of F02 codes resolve at the connector (clean and retest) before probe replacement is needed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>3. Oven running hot, temperature inaccurate on dual-fuel</h3>
        <p>Viking 7 Series dual-fuel (VDR7486, VDR7488) temperature problems are almost always electrical. Four causes in order: RTD probe drift (F02 above), bake element partially shorted ($225-$325), convection fan stalled causing hot spots, door gasket degraded allowing heat loss. 25-75°F overshoot or wide swings → thermostat or RTD. Localized hot spots → convection fan. Gradual undershoot → gasket or element. We diagnose which from the actual symptom pattern.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>4. EOC (Electronic Oven Control) failure, 2019-2022 5 Series</h3>
        <p>Common on Professional 5 Series VGRC5486GSS and VDRC series from 2019-2022 production. Symptoms: temp display blank or corrupted, self-clean fails to start, convection mode won't activate, oven runs continuously regardless of setpoint. EOC is the oven's main computer, replacement $640-$920, 90-minute job. Before ordering, we verify via service-mode diagnostics that EOC is the actual failure (not RTD or wiring mimicking EOC symptoms). 2023+ units have revised control hardware with fewer issues.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>5. Convection fan stalled, uneven cooking, hot spots</h3>
        <p>Dual-fuel only (VDR prefix). Symptom is unmistakable: one rack burning while another undercooks, or significant temperature variation between back and front of cavity. Fan motor mount bearings wear out around year 10-14 on heavy-use units. Replacement $285-$420, 75-minute job. We inspect the fan blade assembly at the same time, bent blades from impact damage are a separate issue that can mimic motor failure.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>6. Oven door gasket compromised, temperature drops, heat escapes</h3>
        <p>Door gasket degradation causes 25-50°F temperature loss and forces the oven to run longer and hotter to compensate. Symptoms: longer preheat times, meat cooking slower than before, thermostat cycling more frequently. Dollar-bill test: close door on a dollar, pull out at each corner and midpoint, minimal resistance = gasket failure in that section. Replacement $285-$420, 75-minute job. LA-specific factor: dry wildfire-season air in Thousand Oaks, Calabasas, and Hidden Hills accelerates gasket degradation, inland homes may need replacement at year 8-10 vs year 12-15 for coastal.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>7. Bake element failed (dual-fuel), oven not heating, F24 or no error</h3>
        <p>Bake element open-circuit or visually damaged (broken, sagging, burnt spot). Element tests 15-25 ohms good. Replacement $225-$325, 45-minute job. We check the terminal block connections at the back of the oven cavity, burnt or corroded terminals are common on 10+ year units and cause repeated element failures if not addressed. Broil element ($245-$345) fails from the same causes and is diagnosed identically.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>8. All-gas oven not heating, weak igniter, glow-bar failure</h3>
        <p>All-gas models (VGR prefix). The glow-bar oven igniter glows to signal the gas safety valve to open; if igniter resistance is too high, it glows but doesn't generate enough current to open the valve fully, resulting in slow heating, temperature undershoot, or complete no-heat. Igniter test: measure current draw during operation (should be 3.2-3.6 amps). Replacement $245-$340, 30-minute job. This is the most common all-gas Viking range failure.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>9. Oven door hinge broken, door won't close flush or sags</h3>
        <p>Viking range doors are heavy (25-40 lb depending on size), and hinges wear over 10-15 years. Symptoms: door sags, won't close flush to the frame, hot air escapes, oven loses temperature. Single hinge replacement $185-$265; both hinges should be replaced together for balanced operation ($340-$485 for pair). Door glass damage from slammed closure is a related issue, inner pane $345-$520.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>10. Gas valve assembly leaking or stuck, burner flame weak or inconsistent</h3>
        <p>Gas valve (behind the burner knob) controls gas flow. Failure modes: stuck partially-open, stuck partially-closed, or slow leak between valve and burner tube. Symptoms: flame too high or too low regardless of knob position, gas smell near unit, burner takes multiple tries to light properly. Valve assembly replacement $425-$640 per burner, 60-minute job. Gas smell is always an emergency, call immediately; shut off main gas valve at the meter while waiting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── SOCAL CONTEXT ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Southern California context</p>
      <h2>Wildfire-season dry air and Viking gasket lifespan</h2>
      <p>Southern California has a distinctive weather pattern that affects oven gasket lifespan: Santa Ana wind events bring relative humidity below 15% for days at a time, particularly in inland foothill areas, Thousand Oaks, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, Agoura Hills, the Pasadena foothills, and canyon homes in Bel Air and Beverly Hills on the LA side; Coto de Caza, North Tustin, and Anaheim Hills in OC; and most of the Inland Empire (Rancho Cucamonga, Alta Loma, Temecula wine-country, Murrieta), where dry summer heat and wildfire-season humidity drops are routine. Repeated exposure to single-digit humidity accelerates silicone and rubber gasket degradation. Oven gaskets that would last 12-15 years in coastal Santa Monica, Brentwood, or Newport Beach may need replacement at year 8-10 in these inland homes, and as early as year 7 in the hottest IE districts.</p>
      <p>We flag this at service visits in affected districts: if your Viking is 7+ years old and lives in an inland fire-weather zone (anywhere from the Conejo Valley through the Inland Empire), we inspect the door gasket as part of any service call and recommend replacement proactively if compression is below spec. Waiting until the gasket visibly fails means 6-18 months of elevated energy use, oven temperature problems, and faster thermostat wear.</p>
      <p>Coastal homes (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica, Venice on the LA side; Newport Beach, Corona del Mar, Laguna Beach in OC) don't see the same humidity swings, standard 12-15 year gasket life applies. The factor that matters more for coastal Viking ranges is salt air on exterior stainless trim, which we address with maintenance polishing rather than parts replacement.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── PRICING ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Pricing</p>
      <h2>What Viking range repair usually costs</h2>
      <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Labor and parts quoted separately before work starts.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical range</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
