      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Viking range repair, common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Burner clicks but won't light</summary>
        <p>Most common call. Wet/greasy (clean and dry 2-4 hrs), grease in port, cap misaligned, or spark module VKPA020047 failed. Swap test: if another knob fires all burners including the failing one, module is fine. Module $285-$425; individual igniter $185-$275.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F02 error</summary>
        <p>RTD temperature probe fault. Test resistance at 77°F (should be ~1080-1100 ohms), inspect connector, verify harness. Probe $165-$245. On pre-2015 Vikings, 20% resolve at connector cleanup before probe replacement.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Oven temperature inaccurate dual-fuel</summary>
        <p>Almost always electrical. RTD drift (F02), bake element short, convection fan stall, or door gasket. 25-75°F swing → thermostat/RTD. Hot spots → fan. Gradual undershoot → gasket/element. Symptom pattern identifies cause.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>5 Series EOC failure</summary>
        <p>Common 2019-2022 VGRC5486GSS. Display blank, self-clean fails, convection won't activate. EOC $640-$920. We verify with service-mode diagnostics before ordering, RTD faults and wiring can mimic EOC. 2023+ units have revised hardware.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Dual-fuel vs all-gas, service difference?</summary>
        <p>Big. Dual-fuel (VDR) oven uses bake/broil element, convection fan, RTD, electrical. All-gas (VGR) uses glow-bar igniter and gas safety valve. Dual-fuel is more precise for baking; all-gas has fewer electrical parts to fail long-term.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Uneven cooking, one rack burning</summary>
        <p>Convection fan stalled (dual-fuel only). Motor bearings wear year 10-14 on heavy-use units. $285-$420 replacement. We inspect fan blade for impact damage at same visit.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Viking range repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common: spark module $285-$425, bake element $225-$325, RTD $165-$245, EOC $640-$920, door gasket $285-$420, oven igniter $245-$340, hinge pair $340-$485. Full pricing above.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
